    <!-- Info Fragment Strings -->
    <string name="info_fragment_title">About our Project</string>
    <string name="info_fragment_paragraph">RioT Technology Corp commissioned us to design and produce a prototype
        Bluetooth data transmission solution. Our product will replace the cables which currently connect environmental
        sensors to data logging devices.\n\nOur project consists of three parts: a device to collect/transmit the data, a
        device to receive the data, and an Android mobile application to configure the devices and the network. The
        transmitting device, we call the <b>BSI</b>, or <b>Bluetooth Sensor Interface</b>. The BSI is designed to take data from sensors,
        attached by the end user, and transmit the measurements over Bluetooth to the receiver. The receiver is called the <b>Local Listener</b>.
        The data received by the Local Listener is stored on a SD memory card. Using the Android application in conjunction with the Local Listener,
        a large network of BSI’s can be configured that will be immune to many of the negative effects experienced by wired systems.
</string>
